bcl:section.bcl:marginalnote: Protected areas deleted from licensed areas

bcl:subsection.bcl:text:
Crown land in a protected area itemized in Column 1 of the Schedule is
          conclusively deemed, effective on the date in Column 2 of the same item, to have been
          deleted from any part of any tree farm licence area, timber licence area, woodlot licence
          area or timber supply area that, on that date, is within the boundaries of that protected
          area.

Each of the following is deemed amended to reflect the deletion under subsection
          (1):

bcl:text.#text:
For the purposes of the application of section 60 of the  and the determination of compensation under that section, the

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text: highway, pipeline or power transmission line rights of way,

bcl:text.#text:
A deletion under section 2 (1) from a tree farm licence area, timber
          licence area or woodlot licence area is conclusively deemed, for all purposes, to have
          been and to be a deletion of Crown land validly made under section 60 of the  as that section read at the time of the deletion, even though
          notice was not served in accordance with that section.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text:
If doubt exists as to whether and to what extent, if any, an allowable cut
          reduction for a tree farm licence was or is attributable to the deletion of land referred
          to in subsection
            (1), the chief forester may issue a written statement resolving the
          doubt.

A written statement under subsection (2) is conclusive for the purposes of
            subsection
            (1).

bcl:marginalnote.#text: Allowable annual cut reductions under section 60 of the

bcl:text.#text:
An annual cut reduction, to the extent that it was or is attributable to the
          establishment of a protected area, is conclusively deemed, for all purposes, to have been
          and to be a reduction in allowable annual cut validly made under section 60 of the
             as that section read at the time of the
          reduction, even though notice was not served in accordance with that section.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text:
If doubt exists as to whether and to what extent, if any, an annual cut reduction
          for any forest licence or timber sale licence was or is attributable to the establishment
          of a protected area in a timber supply area, the minister or a person designated by the
          minister, after consulting with the chief forester, may issue a written statement
          resolving the doubt.

A written statement under subsection (2) is conclusive for the purposes of
            subsection
            (1).

bcl:text.#text:
The amount of compensation payable under section 60 of the  to the holder of a tree farm licence, timber licence, woodlot
        licence, forest licence or timber sale licence must be reduced by any financial benefit or
        other benefit received by that holder from the government before the coming into force of
        this section arising out of the establishment of a protected area.

bcl:section.bcl:marginalnote: No application to settled claims of licence holders
bcl:section.bcl:text:
This Act does not apply in respect of a claim by the holder of a licence against the
        government for compensation or damages because of a deletion under section 2 (1) or
        an annual cut reduction if, before the coming into force of this section, the holder has
        agreed with the government for the settlement of the claim.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text:
This Act must be applied to and must be given effect in every action or other
          proceeding whether commenced before, on or after the date this Act receives Royal
          Assent.

This Act must not be construed as lacking effect, whether retroactive or
          otherwise, in relation to any matter because it makes no specific reference to that
          matter.

bcl:section.bcl:text:
The Lieutenant Governor in Council may amend the Schedule by regulation
        by

bcl:subsection.bcl:text:
Sections 1 to 3, 4 (1) and 7 (3) are deemed to have come into force on January 1, 1995 and
          are retroactive to the extent necessary to give them effect on and after that
          date.

Regulations that may be made under section 9 may be made retroactive
          to January 1, 1995 or a later date that the Lieutenant Governor in Council may determine,
          and a regulation made retroactive is deemed to have come into force on the date specified
          in the regulation.
